BIG THANK YOU TO @lpl_financial!  Last week I had the opportunity to share my journey and bring awareness about living with Tourette Syndrome as part of LPL’s Disability Pride month celebration.  Not only was it LPL’s first time celebrating Disability Pride Month in its 34 year history but it was my first speaking engagement at a Fortune 500 company. I was well outside my comfort zone but the good people at LPL Financial made feel comfortable and welcome. Pushing through my own inhibitions to bring awareness! Big shout out to @therealkxngpxn for making this possible. 
.

Here’s your Small Business Saturday reminder to support your local event creators. Today, we’re celebrating these vibrant entrepreneurs in our creator community:

🛼 @push1515 has built his brand around his passion – rollerskating with style. He shares this passion with his community nationwide through workshops, private skating lessons, and corporate events.
🎶 @afrosocalove hosts block parties, carnivals, and more to celebrate music from around the world and uplift communities within the African diaspora. They’re on a mission to connect people across the US, so be sure catch them in your city.
👑 @twerkafterwork leads empowering, choreography-based dance classes for all levels. Learn twerk basics and build confidence as you get hyped up by their community of thousands.
🎤 @fools.circle is a pop-up comedy and music series that celebrates talent within the Black community. They’ve hosted shows in arcades, parks, and on rooftops across the country.
💐 @flowergirlsmeet is a Chicago-based community with a mission to help women feel seen, heard, and inspired. They hold space for women’s well-being, and host corporate events to improve employee health, productivity, and retention.
💪 @strengthinthecity’s mission is to build community, give back, and leave a legacy through their community-driven fitness and wellness events. From outdoor dance parties to innovative HIIT classes, Strength in the City is redefining health and wellness in Denver and beyond.
